<file path="APP_MAP.md">
# RIAYA — Healthcare Management Platform (Mobile Client)

## 1. System Architecture Core
- State Management: Flutter Riverpod (Notifier / AsyncNotifier)
- Routing Engine: GoRouter with Role-Based Route Mapping
- Network Engine: Dio Client with Unified Envelope Interceptor (`{ success, message, data }`)
- Target Audiences: Doctors & Receptionists (Admin Portal is Web-Only)
- Theme Core: Medical Clinical Teal Palette (Material 3 Adaptive Design)

---

## 2. Global Core Foundations
- [x] Core Network: Create generic `ApiResponse` wrapper
- [x] Core Network: Build `DioClient` with global interceptors & local base URL
- [x] Core Router: Build dynamic `GoRouter` engine mapping routes cleanly
- [x] Core Theme: Configure adaptive Medical Light/Dark sheets using `CardThemeData`

---

## 3. Feature Delivery Matrix

### 🔐 Feature: Authentication & Session Management
- [x] Storage: Implement Local Session Storage (`SharedPreferences` with `StorageService`)
- [x] Data/Domain: Define outgoing `LoginRequest` and incoming `AuthData` response models
- [x] Repository: Build remote API data client mapping (`AuthRepository`)
- [x] State: Code the Riverpod state management pipeline (`AuthNotifier`)
- [x] Presentation: Create standard Clinical Medical Login screen UI form layout

### 👨‍⚕️ Feature: Doctor Portal Dashboard
- [x] UI: Build queue view for scheduled medical appointments
- [x] UI: Create clean vitals overview and patient diagnosis tracking cards

### 📋 Feature: Receptionist Portal Dashboard
- [x] UI: Implement new patient check-in / intake submission system
- [x] UI: Build quick appointments creation wizard UI shell

---

## 4. Active Context / Memory State
- Current Phase: Phase 3 — Doctor Dashboard Integration
- Status: Receptionist Portal fully completed, tested, and validated against backend access rules.
- Next Target: Connecting the Doctor Dashboard to the API, fixing Doctor-specific workflows (like marking appointments "Complete" and submitting diagnosis notes).
</file>

